1
00:00:51,417 --> 00:00:56,218
- You're always sick.
- You were sick when you were my age.

2
00:00:59,158 --> 00:01:02,559
- Evening, sir.
- Evening, Victor.

3
00:01:03,295 --> 00:01:05,889
I didn't realize you were still here.

4
00:01:06,632 --> 00:01:10,398
I was just keeping James company, sir,
if that's all right.

5
00:01:12,237 --> 00:01:13,898
Very kind of you.

6
00:01:15,107 --> 00:01:17,837
- Any better, Son?
- Still cold, Father.

7
00:01:18,410 --> 00:01:19,741
Just a mild fever.

8
00:01:19,812 --> 00:01:23,043
- You'll be all right in the morning.
- You always say that.

9
00:01:23,115 --> 00:01:25,413
And you always pull through, don't you?

10
00:01:25,484 --> 00:01:28,920
- Yeah.
- Now, you taking your medicine?

11
00:01:30,689 --> 00:01:33,453
Elizabeth! Elizabeth!

12
00:01:34,126 --> 00:01:36,390
- Your father's drunk again.
- Elizabeth!

13
00:01:36,462 --> 00:01:40,831
- You should help him home, Victor.
- It's not my name he's calling, sir.

14
00:01:42,367 --> 00:01:44,096
- Father!
- Stay where you are, James.

15
00:01:44,169 --> 00:01:46,069
- Get off me!
- Father!

16
00:01:47,039 --> 00:01:49,234
Now! You never loved him!

17
00:01:50,209 --> 00:01:52,370
I told you never to come back here.

18
00:01:59,218 --> 00:02:00,617
Get out!

19
00:02:12,097 --> 00:02:13,689
James?

20
00:02:18,770 --> 00:02:21,295
- No.
- James?

21
00:02:22,407 --> 00:02:24,307
- There are things you don't understand.
- Don't.

22
00:02:24,376 --> 00:02:26,003
- I need him to know!
- Please don't.

23
00:02:26,078 --> 00:02:28,046
- No more lies.
- James...

24
00:02:45,998 --> 00:02:47,829
- No!
- James!

25
00:02:53,438 --> 00:02:56,635
He... He wasn't your father,

26
00:03:04,983 --> 00:03:06,314
Son.

27
00:03:15,027 --> 00:03:16,619
What are you?

28
00:03:31,710 --> 00:03:35,009
- I didn't mean it! I didn't mean it!
- Yes, you did!

29
00:03:36,014 --> 00:03:39,040
He deserved it, and you gave it to him.

30
00:03:42,154 --> 00:03:44,884
We're brothers, Jimmy. You realize that?

31
00:03:45,490 --> 00:03:47,890
And brothers protect each other.

32
00:03:48,193 --> 00:03:51,959
You have to be hard now,
hard so nothing can ever touch us.

33
00:03:53,098 --> 00:03:55,589
- I want to go home.
- We can't.

34
00:03:56,001 --> 00:03:58,265
We stick together, no matter what,

35
00:03:58,337 --> 00:04:01,500
and take care of anyone
who gets in our way.

36
00:04:01,573 --> 00:04:04,064
Can you do that, little brother?

37
00:04:06,078 --> 00:04:08,876
- I'm going down to the river.
- They're coming.

38
00:04:08,947 --> 00:04:11,780
- Head over the hill. Hurry!
- Can you run?

39
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:19,689
- Keep on running and don't look back.
- Okay.

40
00:05:22,287 --> 00:05:23,754
Back to back!

41
00:06:20,979 --> 00:06:22,503
That's enough!

42
00:06:25,083 --> 00:06:26,345
Enough!

43
00:06:39,598 --> 00:06:41,122
No! No!

44
00:06:42,367 --> 00:06:44,198
Stand down, soldier!

45
00:06:49,975 --> 00:06:51,408
Victor!

46
00:06:54,513 --> 00:06:55,980
Stand down! Stand down!

47
00:06:56,047 --> 00:06:58,345
Stand down!

48
00:07:01,853 --> 00:07:03,047
No!

49
00:07:29,181 --> 00:07:32,082
Ready, aim...

50
00:07:32,684 --> 00:07:34,481
Wake me when it's over.

51
00:07:43,962 --> 00:07:45,020
...fire!

52
00:07:51,136 --> 00:07:54,435
Freaks! You're animals! Freaks!

53
00:07:54,506 --> 00:07:56,838
My name is Major William Stryker.

54
00:07:56,908 --> 00:08:00,071
You've been charged
with killing a senior officer.

55
00:08:00,145 --> 00:08:02,079
Is that correct?

56
00:08:02,147 --> 00:08:04,308
Apparently, we have some issues
with authority...

57
00:08:04,382 --> 00:08:07,078
- Just keep a lid on it.
- ...sir.

58
00:08:08,186 --> 00:08:11,019
The warden tells me that your sentence
was carried out by a firing squad

59
00:08:11,089 --> 00:08:12,954
at 1000 hours.

60
00:08:13,024 --> 00:08:15,219
- How'd that go?
- lt tickled.

61
00:08:20,198 --> 00:08:24,635
You boys tired of running?
Tired of denying your true nature?

62
00:08:25,637 --> 00:08:28,071
- What do you care?
- Oh, I care.

63
00:08:28,874 --> 00:08:31,434
I care because I know how special you are.

64
00:08:31,510 --> 00:08:33,205
How valuable.

65
00:08:37,082 --> 00:08:41,451
Look, you can stay here
locked up like freaks of nature,

66
00:08:42,587 --> 00:08:44,384
or you can join me.

67
00:08:44,990 --> 00:08:49,120
I'm putting together a special team
with special privileges.

68
00:08:50,161 --> 00:08:54,495
Now, tell me, how would you like
to really serve your country?

69
00:09:08,647 --> 00:09:09,636
You know, I love this weapon

70
00:09:09,714 --> 00:09:11,238
more than any other thing
in the whole wide world.

71
00:09:11,316 --> 00:09:13,307
- Do you wanna know why?
- No.

72
00:09:14,085 --> 00:09:15,746
It's memorable.

73
00:09:15,820 --> 00:09:17,947
Sure, it's a little bulky,
tough to get on a plane.

74
00:09:18,023 --> 00:09:21,550
You whip out a couple of swords
at your ex-girlfriend's wedding,

75
00:09:21,626 --> 00:09:23,924
they will never, ever forget it.

76
00:09:23,995 --> 00:09:25,826
That's funny, Wade.

77
00:09:25,897 --> 00:09:29,264
I think you confuse me
with someone who gives a shit.

78
00:09:29,334 --> 00:09:32,098
Right, it's probably not
as intimidating as having a gun

79
00:09:32,170 --> 00:09:36,072
or bone claws
or the fingernails of a bag lady.

80
00:09:44,950 --> 00:09:48,010
- Manicure?
- Victor. Easy.

81
00:09:50,622 --> 00:09:53,386
Fred got a new tattoo. I'm concerned.

82
00:09:54,292 --> 00:09:57,284
Oh, Jesus, Fred,
you just met her last night.

83
00:09:57,529 --> 00:10:00,123
- I love her.
- You love her after one night?

84
00:10:00,198 --> 00:10:01,825
She's a gymnast.

85
00:10:03,201 --> 00:10:05,101
Bradley, take her down.

86
00:10:09,708 --> 00:10:11,801
Oh, God.

87
00:10:11,876 --> 00:10:13,810
- Are you gonna puke?
- lf we were meant to fly,

88
00:10:13,878 --> 00:10:15,675
- we'd grow wings.
- Don't worry, Nancy.

89
00:10:15,747 --> 00:10:19,148
- More people die driving than flying.
- How about from impaling?

90
00:10:19,217 --> 00:10:22,345
Hey, be nice,
or be your approximation of nice.

91
00:10:23,855 --> 00:10:25,846
- Would you like a bucket?
- No.

92
00:10:25,924 --> 00:10:28,085
Gentlemen, wheels down in Lagos in five.

93
00:11:03,995 --> 00:11:08,159
- Why are we here?
- All in good time. Zero?

94
00:11:13,838 --> 00:11:17,899
- lntruder! Perimeter breach!
- Man the weapon!

95
00:11:19,177 --> 00:11:23,511
Intruder, stop!
Put your hands behind your head!

96
00:11:53,011 --> 00:11:54,569
Having fun yet?

97
00:11:59,651 --> 00:12:01,676
- Fred?
- The tank?

98
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:04,884
- The tank.
- Yeah, I got that.

99
00:12:39,924 --> 00:12:44,327
Great. Stuck in an elevator
with five guys on a high-protein diet.

100
00:12:44,395 --> 00:12:46,226
- Wade.
- Dreams really do come true.

101
00:12:46,331 --> 00:12:47,389
Just shut it!

102
00:12:47,465 --> 00:12:50,457
- You're up next. - Thank you, sir.
You look really nice today.

103
00:12:50,535 --> 00:12:53,060
It's the green.
It brings out the seriousness in your eyes.

104
00:12:53,138 --> 00:12:57,097
- Oh, my God. Do you ever shut up, pal?
- No. Not when I'm awake.

105
00:12:57,976 --> 00:13:00,069
Bradley? Top floor, please.

106
00:13:08,520 --> 00:13:11,045
Cover the elevator! The elevator!

107
00:13:20,899 --> 00:13:22,730
Time to go to work.

108
00:13:59,370 --> 00:14:02,396
Okay. People are dead.

109
00:14:05,176 --> 00:14:09,408
If you didn't have that mouth on you,
Wade, you'd be the perfect soldier.

110
00:14:14,452 --> 00:14:17,250
I wouldn't do that if I was you, brother.

111
00:14:21,259 --> 00:14:25,821
- Take the diamonds. They're yours.
- I don't want your diamonds.

112
00:14:27,198 --> 00:14:28,631
I want this.

113
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:32,335
But that is nothing. A souvenir.

114
00:14:33,071 --> 00:14:35,904
Where did you find it? I want the source.

115
00:14:36,908 --> 00:14:41,675
A small village, far inland,
three days from here.

116
00:14:44,182 --> 00:14:47,777
Tell him this rock is
more valuable to me than his life.

117
00:14:47,852 --> 00:14:49,911
Ask him where he found it.

118
00:15:00,665 --> 00:15:02,132
Okay.

119
00:15:03,234 --> 00:15:05,099
He says it came from the sky.

120
00:15:09,173 --> 00:15:11,141
He's telling the truth.

121
00:15:11,976 --> 00:15:13,807
You don't know the language, Logan.

122
00:15:13,878 --> 00:15:16,005
- It's a meteor fragment.
- I know what it is.

123
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:18,480
I'm asking him where he found it.

124
00:15:18,549 --> 00:15:21,074
Sir, base wants to know our location.

125
00:15:21,152 --> 00:15:23,416
- Shut them down.
- Yes.

126
00:15:25,790 --> 00:15:27,849
Tell him everyone here will die

127
00:15:27,926 --> 00:15:30,895
unless he tells me
where he found the rock.

128
00:15:41,039 --> 00:15:43,701
- He says that it's sacred.
- Okay, fine.

129
00:15:47,478 --> 00:15:48,877
Victor.

130
00:16:05,897 --> 00:16:07,330
Victor!

131
00:16:10,935 --> 00:16:13,096
Don't even think about it.

132
00:16:14,505 --> 00:16:16,632
We didn't sign up for this.

133
00:16:20,211 --> 00:16:21,803
Put him down!

134
00:16:34,292 --> 00:16:36,089
What are you doing?

135
00:16:37,395 --> 00:16:39,886
We finally got a good thing going here.
Don't you screw this up.

136
00:16:39,964 --> 00:16:41,761
Enough. That's enough.
We've done enough.

137
00:16:41,833 --> 00:16:43,926
Who do you think you are?

138
00:16:44,268 --> 00:16:45,997
This is what we do.

139
00:16:46,771 --> 00:16:49,001
Maybe you'd rather be
rotting in a hole somewhere

140
00:16:49,073 --> 00:16:52,839
till they figure out a way to do it to us.
Is that it? Huh?

141
00:16:53,344 --> 00:16:54,777
I'm done.

142
00:16:57,215 --> 00:16:58,682
You coming?

143
00:17:05,323 --> 00:17:06,620
Jimmy!

144
00:17:12,063 --> 00:17:14,463
We can't just let you walk away.

145
00:17:23,007 --> 00:17:24,201
Jimmy!

146
00:17:27,111 --> 00:17:28,408
Jimmy!

147
00:18:17,829 --> 00:18:19,854
Why are you up so early?

148
00:18:22,467 --> 00:18:23,866
Come here.

149
00:19:02,406 --> 00:19:03,998
See you, baby.

150
00:19:05,176 --> 00:19:06,473
Hey.

151
00:19:13,351 --> 00:19:16,081
Oh, that's nice. Yes. Take your time.

152
00:19:18,122 --> 00:19:19,248
You're wrapped, man.

153
00:19:37,175 --> 00:19:40,042
Okay, I'm totally gonna get this.

154
00:19:42,213 --> 00:19:44,238
Nope. Come on.

155
00:19:45,850 --> 00:19:48,250
Oh, wow! Let's go on the Ferris wheel.

156
00:19:48,319 --> 00:19:49,752
- How does he do it?
- Come on.

157
00:19:49,820 --> 00:19:51,447
...amazing lady in a box!

158
00:20:00,565 --> 00:20:02,829
Swing the hammer, ring the bell!

159
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:04,765
Hey, what do you do?

160
00:20:07,104 --> 00:20:09,334
If you turn off the light, you win a prize.

161
00:20:09,407 --> 00:20:13,104
- Three tries for a buck.
- Come on, I wanna do it.

162
00:20:13,644 --> 00:20:15,441
There you go. Okay?

163
00:20:19,850 --> 00:20:21,613
No, that's obvious.

164
00:20:25,356 --> 00:20:26,789
That's two.

165
00:20:35,433 --> 00:20:37,628
Well, that's a stupid trick.

166
00:20:38,135 --> 00:20:40,035
It's not a trick, man.

167
00:20:40,404 --> 00:20:42,531
Come on. Freak.

168
00:20:44,475 --> 00:20:45,703
Bye.

169
00:21:14,272 --> 00:21:15,705
Show's over!

170
00:21:20,711 --> 00:21:23,271
I said show's over!

171
00:21:28,219 --> 00:21:30,744
The show's never over for us, Bradley.

172
00:21:33,257 --> 00:21:35,953
- Victor.
- Aren't you gonna invite me in?

173
00:21:38,462 --> 00:21:40,589
Yeah. Come on in.

174
00:21:53,377 --> 00:21:58,178
You know, I've never said anything
to anyone about what happened.

175
00:21:58,916 --> 00:22:01,441
I'm living a totally
different life now, Victor.

176
00:22:01,519 --> 00:22:03,783
No need to bring up the past.

177
00:22:18,969 --> 00:22:20,402
You know,

178
00:22:21,539 --> 00:22:25,839
I always thought it would
be Wade to come knocking at my door.

179
00:22:25,910 --> 00:22:29,471
Well... Well,

180
00:22:30,548 --> 00:22:31,981
Wade's gone.

181
00:22:35,486 --> 00:22:37,613
I'm not afraid of you, Victor.

182
00:22:40,358 --> 00:22:42,349
I'm not afraid of dying.

183
00:22:43,594 --> 00:22:45,255
How do you know?

184
00:22:46,497 --> 00:22:48,727
You've never tried it before.

185
00:23:05,916 --> 00:23:07,816
Was it the wars?

186
00:23:09,286 --> 00:23:10,719
Which one?

187
00:23:11,255 --> 00:23:12,688
All of them.

188
00:23:20,598 --> 00:23:23,431
- Tell me.
- Hey.

189
00:23:24,268 --> 00:23:26,099
It's just a scratch.

190
00:23:33,444 --> 00:23:36,436
Looks like we're gonna need
new sheets again, baby.

191
00:23:36,514 --> 00:23:37,947
Yeah.

192
00:24:02,706 --> 00:24:04,640
Who the hell is this?

193
00:24:04,708 --> 00:24:06,676
Smells like government.

194
00:24:10,881 --> 00:24:13,315
My God. Haven't aged a day!

195
00:24:13,384 --> 00:24:14,908
Clean living.

196
00:24:15,453 --> 00:24:19,981
- You remember Agent Zero?
- Still shooting first, asking questions later?

197
00:24:21,559 --> 00:24:25,723
- You still chewing on cheap cigars?
- Boys, please.

198
00:24:27,198 --> 00:24:29,496
- I have a job for you.
- I already have a job.

199
00:24:29,567 --> 00:24:31,694
Lumberjack? 18 grand a year?

200
00:24:31,769 --> 00:24:35,205
18.5. Plus I haven't had to kill anyone
in a while.

201
00:24:35,272 --> 00:24:37,263
- Starting to miss it?
- Right about now I am.

202
00:24:37,341 --> 00:24:39,639
- Yeah?
- Zero, back to the car.

203
00:24:43,214 --> 00:24:44,681
Attaboy.

204
00:24:51,255 --> 00:24:54,588
You know, I'm not proud about
the way things ended between us.

205
00:24:54,658 --> 00:24:56,558
Conversation's over.

206
00:24:57,528 --> 00:25:01,157
Playing Little House on the Prairie
with a schoolteacher,

207
00:25:01,599 --> 00:25:03,362
I mean, that just isn't you, Logan.

208
00:25:03,534 --> 00:25:05,559
And you would know, huh?

209
00:25:05,936 --> 00:25:08,530
- I would.
- What do you want, Stryker?

210
00:25:10,674 --> 00:25:13,108
Bradley was killed three days ago.

211
00:25:14,144 --> 00:25:15,805
Wade before that.

212
00:25:16,547 --> 00:25:19,880
I believe that someone is hunting down
our old team.

213
00:25:20,818 --> 00:25:24,845
- Anyone else?
- As far as I know, Victor is safe.

214
00:25:26,657 --> 00:25:29,421
But whoever it is has names, addresses.

215
00:25:29,493 --> 00:25:31,552
I can take care of myself.

216
00:25:33,497 --> 00:25:35,761
This is not about you, Logan.

217
00:25:39,236 --> 00:25:41,170
Your country needs you.

218
00:25:42,206 --> 00:25:43,696
I'm Canadian.

219
00:25:44,708 --> 00:25:47,506
I know you, Logan! I know who you are!

220
00:26:01,058 --> 00:26:05,017
- Miss Kayla, Miss Kayla, look what I did.
- What did you do?

221
00:26:16,373 --> 00:26:18,534
Bye, Miss Silverfox! Bye!

222
00:26:25,449 --> 00:26:26,939
What's wrong?

223
00:26:29,320 --> 00:26:31,254
Stryker came by today.

224
00:26:32,356 --> 00:26:33,823
Don't worry. I said no.

225
00:26:33,891 --> 00:26:36,917
Why is he bothering you
after all these years?

226
00:26:36,994 --> 00:26:39,326
Because I'm the best there is at what I do,

227
00:26:39,396 --> 00:26:41,057
but what I do best isn't very nice.

228
00:26:41,131 --> 00:26:44,828
You're not an animal, Logan.
What you have is a gift.

229
00:26:44,902 --> 00:26:47,769
A gift. You can return a gift.

230
00:27:01,051 --> 00:27:02,643
Come on, fellas.

231
00:27:03,854 --> 00:27:05,287
All right.

232
00:27:05,789 --> 00:27:07,416
Stay in the car.

233
00:27:07,992 --> 00:27:10,119
I'm just gonna ask nicely.

234
00:27:14,131 --> 00:27:16,156
You mind letting us go by?

235
00:27:16,867 --> 00:27:18,494
- You in some kind of a hurry there, pal?
- Hey, hey, hey.

236
00:27:18,569 --> 00:27:19,866
Are you?

237
00:27:19,937 --> 00:27:21,199
Just move your truck so we can go by.

238
00:27:21,271 --> 00:27:23,432
We're trying to have
a conversation there, all right?

239
00:27:23,507 --> 00:27:25,702
You start something,
you'd better be ready to finish it.

240
00:27:25,776 --> 00:27:27,141
Listen...

241
00:27:27,211 --> 00:27:30,180
Hey, guys, take it easy! Calm down.

242
00:27:34,718 --> 00:27:37,710
- Your boyfriend's got a big mouth.
- I know.

243
00:27:37,788 --> 00:27:41,724
Big temper, too. So please let us pass.

244
00:27:46,363 --> 00:27:49,890
- Thank you.
- Come on, man, let's go.

245
00:27:50,668 --> 00:27:52,499
How'd you do that?

246
00:27:52,936 --> 00:27:55,564
Female powers of persuasion. It's a gift.

247
00:27:55,639 --> 00:27:59,040
Oh, I see.
Do you have those powers over me?

248
00:27:59,109 --> 00:28:01,976
Well, you didn't stay in the car, did you?

249
00:28:18,862 --> 00:28:21,194
Why is the moon so lonely?

250
00:28:22,566 --> 00:28:23,692
Why?

251
00:28:24,201 --> 00:28:26,499
Because she used to have a lover.

252
00:28:26,570 --> 00:28:28,970
- You tell this to the kids?
- No.

253
00:28:30,074 --> 00:28:32,975
His name was Kuekuatsheu
and they lived in the Spirit World together.

254
00:28:33,043 --> 00:28:36,035
Oh, this is a true story? All right.

255
00:28:36,113 --> 00:28:38,843
And every night they would
wander the skies together,

256
