01:00:00,696 --> 01:00:04,598
I seem to remember that girl
when she was about 85 pounds, huh?

510
01:00:05,801 --> 01:00:08,565
Oh, that's funny.
You're still so funny, Logan.

511
01:00:08,637 --> 01:00:10,730
You know where Victor is?

512
01:00:11,607 --> 01:00:14,132
- No idea.
- What's the island, slim?

513
01:00:16,778 --> 01:00:18,678
Don't let the door hit you
on the way out, Logan.

514
01:00:18,747 --> 01:00:21,079
Listen, I ain't leaving here
till you tell me where Victor is.

515
01:00:21,149 --> 01:00:24,050
So come on, bub, for old times' sake, huh?

516
01:00:25,420 --> 01:00:28,981
Did you just call me Blob?

517
01:00:30,826 --> 01:00:32,259
No, but...

518
01:00:38,266 --> 01:00:40,894
I told you not to mention his weight.
Why'd you call him Blob?

519
01:00:40,969 --> 01:00:43,403
I didn't call him Blob. I said "bub".

520
01:00:43,472 --> 01:00:45,702
- God damn it.
- Hey, hey, hey. Hey, Logan.

521
01:00:45,774 --> 01:00:47,036
I got an idea.

522
01:00:48,644 --> 01:00:51,135
- This is your idea of an idea?
- I'm trying to help you out, Logan.

523
01:00:51,213 --> 01:00:52,805
Dukes don't like you that much
and you know it.

524
01:00:52,881 --> 01:00:55,145
- Yeah, the feeling's mutual.
- Well, use them gloves, man.

525
01:00:55,217 --> 01:00:59,483
Dance with him a little bit.
Allow him to let his anger out on you.

526
01:00:59,554 --> 01:01:02,580
Figure if you do that, he'll probably
tell you everything you want to know.

527
01:01:02,658 --> 01:01:04,455
Come on, man, look at him.

528
01:01:04,526 --> 01:01:07,256
Got a big old ass coming out
the front of his shirt.

529
01:01:07,329 --> 01:01:09,729
Jesus. He's gonna have a coronary,
for Christ's sake.

530
01:01:09,798 --> 01:01:12,665
Is there even a stretcher big enough
to take this guy out of here?

531
01:01:14,469 --> 01:01:16,767
It ain't him I'm worried about
getting out of here on a stretcher.

532
01:01:16,838 --> 01:01:19,329
- You're an asshole.
- Come on, Logan.

533
01:01:21,543 --> 01:01:23,534
- Whup his ass!
- You want it?

534
01:01:23,612 --> 01:01:25,546
Dance with him, Fred!
Just like I taught you.

535
01:01:26,214 --> 01:01:27,238
You want to dance with me?

536
01:01:27,315 --> 01:01:30,113
- Come on, Fred!
- Oh! Oh, that feels good.

537
01:01:33,355 --> 01:01:35,016
Hey! Guess what?

538
01:01:36,525 --> 01:01:37,822
See, he gonna talk now.

539
01:01:37,893 --> 01:01:40,293
- You got him right where you want him.
- Whose side are you on, anyway?

540
01:01:40,362 --> 01:01:41,829
Come on!

541
01:01:42,464 --> 01:01:44,432
Come on, now, lamb chop!

542
01:02:00,015 --> 01:02:01,209
Damn!

543
01:02:15,831 --> 01:02:17,355
Now, where's Victor?

544
01:02:48,830 --> 01:02:51,822
Little dark for sunglasses, don't you think?

545
01:03:07,415 --> 01:03:11,749
- Please, don't! Please, don't!
- Victor!

546
01:03:15,357 --> 01:03:17,723
Hey, hey! Where's Victor?

547
01:03:19,261 --> 01:03:24,631
Yeah. Victor's with Stryker on the island.

548
01:03:24,699 --> 01:03:27,167
They run it together.

549
01:03:28,370 --> 01:03:31,339
What? They what?
Victor will be with Stryker?

550
01:03:32,240 --> 01:03:33,400
Yeah.

551
01:03:34,142 --> 01:03:36,133
You didn't know that?

552
01:03:56,131 --> 01:04:00,568
All that's left now is Logan.
I trust you can handle that.

553
01:04:01,870 --> 01:04:05,670
- I did before, didn't I?
- Oh, yes. You did that.

554
01:04:09,010 --> 01:04:12,309
Our deal. It still applies, right?

555
01:04:14,649 --> 01:04:17,777
Of course.
Now bag him and tag him, Captain.

556
01:04:26,761 --> 01:04:28,524
What's the island?

557
01:04:29,731 --> 01:04:33,428
It's where Stryker takes
them after Victor's caught them.

558
01:04:34,469 --> 01:04:36,767
Wait, hang on a minute. Takes who?

559
01:04:38,473 --> 01:04:39,804
Mutants.

560
01:04:40,609 --> 01:04:44,739
Rumor is that Stryker's doing
experiments on them there.

561
01:04:47,716 --> 01:04:50,014
I mean, you never wondered
what happened to them?

562
01:04:50,085 --> 01:04:51,848
I tried not to.

563
01:05:08,203 --> 01:05:11,639
They killed her so I'd let them
put Adamantium in me.

564
01:05:14,943 --> 01:05:17,776
They killed her for a goddamn experiment.

565
01:05:21,883 --> 01:05:26,149
- Where is it? Where is it?
- Logan, Stryker kept it real secret.

566
01:05:30,692 --> 01:05:34,719
But a prisoner escaped there once.

567
01:05:34,796 --> 01:05:37,264
- Who?
- His name was Remy LeBeau.

568
01:05:37,332 --> 01:05:39,596
He was a street hustler from New Orleans.

569
01:05:39,668 --> 01:05:42,535
The guards at the prison
called him Gambit

570
01:05:42,604 --> 01:05:43,969
because he kept taking
all their money at poker.

571
01:05:44,039 --> 01:05:46,007
- That's all I know.
- What's Stryker up to, Fred?

572
01:05:46,074 --> 01:05:47,837
What's the endgame?

573
01:05:49,844 --> 01:05:54,338
He's taking their powers.
Trying to combine them somehow.

574
01:05:54,416 --> 01:05:57,283
That's all I know, Logan. That's all I know.

575
01:05:57,919 --> 01:06:01,582
If I have to come back here,
I'm gonna take your head off.

576
01:06:05,360 --> 01:06:07,521
I'm coming with you, Logan.

577
01:06:08,964 --> 01:06:11,728
- There's no redemption where I'm going.
- I ain't asking.

578
01:06:49,437 --> 01:06:51,166
There's our dude.

579
01:06:57,445 --> 01:06:59,174
That's cool.

580
01:06:59,247 --> 01:07:01,306
I'm gonna go cover the back
in case he rabbits.

581
01:07:01,383 --> 01:07:03,510
- I'm not gonna fight with him.
- Yeah, right.

582
01:07:03,585 --> 01:07:05,644
What? I get in fights with everybody?

583
01:07:05,720 --> 01:07:07,847
Don't dogs kill cats?

584
01:07:07,922 --> 01:07:10,390
Just go cover the back, will you?

585
01:07:14,396 --> 01:07:16,887
- Give me 500.
- I'm in.

586
01:07:22,804 --> 01:07:24,567
Are you Remy LeBeau?

587
01:07:26,741 --> 01:07:28,971
- Do I owe you money?
- No.

588
01:07:30,612 --> 01:07:32,512
Then Remy LeBeau I am.

589
01:07:51,132 --> 01:07:53,965
Large blind's 100. Small blind's 50.

590
01:07:54,903 --> 01:07:58,930
- May I deal you in?
- What can I get for 17 bucks?

591
01:08:00,008 --> 01:08:01,305
$17?

592
01:08:02,911 --> 01:08:04,936
A cab ride home, perhaps?

593
01:08:09,484 --> 01:08:12,180
You my brother's new babysitter, John?

594
01:08:13,021 --> 01:08:14,386
I ain't Bradley, Victor.

595
01:08:14,456 --> 01:08:16,549
And your creepy black coat
don't scare me.

596
01:08:16,624 --> 01:08:17,852
Really?

597
01:08:18,660 --> 01:08:20,560
Worked on Dukes.

598
01:08:20,628 --> 01:08:22,858
You shouldn't have done that,
'cause now I'm gonna kill you

599
01:08:22,931 --> 01:08:25,058
before Logan even gets a chance.

600
01:08:25,366 --> 01:08:27,926
So what brings you to our fair city, sir?

601
01:08:28,002 --> 01:08:29,560
Victor Creed.

602
01:08:32,040 --> 01:08:33,735
And who's that?

603
01:08:34,442 --> 01:08:35,568
The man I'm gonna kill.

604
01:08:37,345 --> 01:08:40,678
He works with a man named Stryker
on an island.

605
01:08:42,183 --> 01:08:45,675
- Just need to know where it is.
- And why would you think I know that?

606
01:08:45,753 --> 01:08:48,620
Well, 'cause I know who you are, Gambit.

607
01:08:49,724 --> 01:08:54,423
You're the guy who escaped and you're
the guy who's gonna take me back there.

608
01:08:55,497 --> 01:08:59,160
You know, John, there's something
I always wanted to tell you.

609
01:09:05,240 --> 01:09:08,266
You're predictable.

610
01:09:11,079 --> 01:09:13,570
I can feel your spine, Johnny Boy.

611
01:09:14,549 --> 01:09:17,279
That's funny. Never knew you had one.

612
01:09:20,889 --> 01:09:24,222
Those are mighty nice tags
you have on there, sir.

613
01:09:25,593 --> 01:09:28,687
The men who took me wore
tags just like them.

614
01:09:32,367 --> 01:09:34,733
Hey, now, bub, you listen to me.

615
01:09:52,353 --> 01:09:54,253
Damn it. That little...

616
01:10:08,069 --> 01:10:11,800
Two years I rotted in that hellhole
and I ain't never going back.

617
01:10:16,077 --> 01:10:17,408
Shiny.

618
01:10:20,081 --> 01:10:22,208
Tell me something, Jimmy.

619
01:10:22,884 --> 01:10:25,284
Do you even know how to kill me?

620
01:10:25,353 --> 01:10:28,083
I'm gonna cut your goddamned head off.

621
01:10:28,756 --> 01:10:30,621
See if that works.

622
01:10:40,235 --> 01:10:42,567
You're getting slow, old man.

623
01:10:51,279 --> 01:10:53,247
You son of a bitch.

624
01:10:56,884 --> 01:10:59,751
You're gonna die for what you did to her.

625
01:11:23,978 --> 01:11:25,240
Victor!

626
01:11:35,189 --> 01:11:37,282
Well, that's a nice stick.

627
01:12:35,750 --> 01:12:38,275
Okay, shithead, here's the deal.

628
01:12:38,353 --> 01:12:41,720
See, you're gonna take me to this island,
where I can kill Creed, Stryker

629
01:12:41,789 --> 01:12:45,987
and pretty much everyone you hate
in this world. Do you understand?

630
01:12:46,661 --> 01:12:48,322
You're really gonna kill them?

631
01:12:48,396 --> 01:12:51,194
As long as you stay out of my way, yeah.

632
01:13:05,246 --> 01:13:06,713
Colonel?

633
01:13:07,281 --> 01:13:09,511
- General?
- ls this Weapon Xl?

634
01:13:12,086 --> 01:13:14,987
All their strengths
and none of their weaknesses.

635
01:13:15,056 --> 01:13:16,990
You really hate them, don't you?

636
01:13:17,058 --> 01:13:18,958
No, I don't hate them.

637
01:13:19,360 --> 01:13:23,626
After 20 years of working with mutants,
I just know what they can do.

638
01:13:27,535 --> 01:13:31,596
We can win this war before it starts
and save countless lives in the process.

639
01:13:31,672 --> 01:13:35,233
Pre-emptive action is
the only action here, General.

640
01:13:35,309 --> 01:13:39,040
The days of our country
sitting on the sidelines are over.

641
01:13:40,014 --> 01:13:44,075
We need to take the fight to the enemy
before they take the fight to us.

642
01:13:44,152 --> 01:13:46,985
- I admire your passion, I do.
- Thank you.

643
01:13:47,755 --> 01:13:50,053
But this is as far as it goes.

644
01:13:51,058 --> 01:13:54,619
- Weapon X was a hiccup.
- We know about your son, Bill.

645
01:13:55,263 --> 01:13:58,824
We know he's a mutant,
and we know he killed your wife.

646
01:13:58,900 --> 01:14:01,960
- You shouldn't have kept that from us.
- That...

647
01:14:03,504 --> 01:14:05,233
That has nothing
to do with my work, General.

648
01:14:05,306 --> 01:14:06,637
Bullshit.

649
01:14:06,941 --> 01:14:10,240
You're too close to this.
I'm shutting you down.

650
01:14:10,978 --> 01:14:15,415
Okay. You're right. I won't lie to you.

651
01:14:18,886 --> 01:14:22,549
My son did bring
the problem home for me,

652
01:14:24,058 --> 01:14:25,821
but I took an oath

653
01:14:27,328 --> 01:14:29,592
to protect the American people

654
01:14:30,698 --> 01:14:33,667
from every threat, both foreign

655
01:14:41,776 --> 01:14:43,437
and domestic.

656
01:14:51,385 --> 01:14:53,216
- You don't like flying, huh?
- I'm fine.

657
01:14:53,287 --> 01:14:54,720
- Just concentrate on what you're doing.
- You sure?

658
01:14:54,789 --> 01:14:56,416
You got a bit of sweat
on your brow there.

659
01:14:56,491 --> 01:14:58,152
Very funny. Just keep your eyes on the...

660
01:14:58,226 --> 01:14:59,989
On the what? The clouds?
Keep my eyes on the clouds?

661
01:15:00,061 --> 01:15:01,653
You're up and down
like a freaking yo-yo here!

662
01:15:01,729 --> 01:15:04,129
- Where'd you get this thing, anyway?
- Oh, this is my baby.

663
01:15:04,198 --> 01:15:06,928
I won her in a game. Jacks over fives.

664
01:15:08,236 --> 01:15:09,498
Great.

665
01:15:10,071 --> 01:15:12,232
Relax. We're almost there.

666
01:15:15,610 --> 01:15:19,046
There it is. The island. Three Mile lsland.

667
01:15:19,580 --> 01:15:21,548
Hiding in plain sight.

668
01:15:24,085 --> 01:15:27,077
No one's gonna snoop
around a nuclear reactor.

669
01:15:27,154 --> 01:15:29,145
They think it's gonna turn them
into freaks.

670
01:15:29,223 --> 01:15:31,282
- Like you?
- Right.

671
01:15:34,028 --> 01:15:36,758
All right. You ready?
Because it's now or never. Let's go.

672
01:15:36,831 --> 01:15:38,264
About time.

673
01:15:47,475 --> 01:15:51,036
Hey, if it makes you feel any better,
this is really gonna hurt.

674
01:15:51,112 --> 01:15:53,910
Well, yeah, it kind of does, actually.

675
01:15:55,116 --> 01:15:58,017
- Good luck.
- Likewise.

676
01:16:00,288 --> 01:16:01,482
Oh, shit.

677
01:16:08,930 --> 01:16:11,455
How you doing? Everything all right?

678
01:16:13,000 --> 01:16:15,525
- Is he ready yet?
- A few more hours.

679
01:16:15,603 --> 01:16:18,834
- And he will respond to my commands?
- Absolutely.

680
01:17:22,536 --> 01:17:23,764
Logan.

681
01:17:25,039 --> 01:17:27,132
Welcome back to the war.

682
01:17:28,142 --> 01:17:31,009
Before I gut you, I want to know why.

683
01:17:32,713 --> 01:17:35,045
I needed your powers for the Pool.

684
01:17:35,116 --> 01:17:37,584
- For the what?
- The mutant killer.

685
01:17:38,519 --> 01:17:40,111
Deadpool.

686
01:17:41,355 --> 01:17:43,323
Years of searching and refining,

687
01:17:43,391 --> 01:17:47,350
finding the right powers
that can coexist in one body

688
01:17:47,428 --> 01:17:49,589
without ripping it apart.

689
01:17:50,765 --> 01:17:53,529
My son was the first piece of the puzzle.

690
01:17:55,369 --> 01:17:57,530
Logan, you were the last.

691
01:17:57,605 --> 01:17:59,835
You made Weapon Xl possible.

692
01:18:00,875 --> 01:18:06,108
I asked you to help,
but you said you wanted the quiet life.

693
01:18:08,215 --> 01:18:09,409
Well,

694
01:18:10,117 --> 01:18:14,986
I've learned that nothing motivates
the men in your family like revenge.

695
01:18:32,573 --> 01:18:34,006
Who are you?

696
01:18:34,875 --> 01:18:37,036
Oh, she's real, old friend.

697
01:18:48,956 --> 01:18:52,187
Did you really think
we'd just let you walk away?

698
01:18:52,460 --> 01:18:54,553
You're a dangerous man.

699
01:18:54,628 --> 01:18:57,392
We like to keep an eye on dangerous men.

700
01:18:58,132 --> 01:19:00,532
Tell him about the day you died.

701
01:19:06,407 --> 01:19:09,501
They gave me a shot
of hydrochlorothiazide.

702
01:19:11,579 --> 01:19:15,242
It reduces the heart rate so low
it appears you flatlined.

703
01:19:27,161 --> 01:19:29,186
Don't be angry with her.

704
01:19:30,197 --> 01:19:32,927
She's a real credit to your species.

705
01:19:36,237 --> 01:19:39,695
Did you know that her sister has
diamond-hard skin?

706
01:19:40,541 --> 01:19:43,203
Kayla's mutation is tactohypnosis.

707
01:19:43,844 --> 01:19:46,904
She can influence people
as long as she touches them.

708
01:19:46,981 --> 01:19:49,609
Quite a useful tool in a seduction.

709
01:19:49,683 --> 01:19:52,015
It was never real, my friend.

710
01:19:57,424 --> 01:19:59,324
It was real for me.

711
01:20:01,328 --> 01:20:05,788
I told you if you came down this road,
you wouldn't like what you found.

712
01:20:12,039 --> 01:20:16,840
That story you told me about a man
who gets flowers for the moon,

713
01:20:18,913 --> 01:20:20,744
I had it backwards.

714
01:20:23,951 --> 01:20:27,409
I thought you were the moon
and I was your wolverine.

715
01:20:29,723 --> 01:20:32,419
But you're the trickster, aren't you?

716
01:20:33,060 --> 01:20:35,494
I'm just the fool who got played.

717
01:20:37,531 --> 01:20:40,523
The worst part of it is,
I should have known.

718
01:20:43,637 --> 01:20:45,867
But I ignored my instincts.

719
01:20:49,510 --> 01:20:51,740
I ignored what I really am.

720
01:20:56,350 --> 01:20:58,841
But that won't ever happen again.

721
01:21:30,551 --> 01:21:32,485
- Colonel?
- Not now, Kayla.

722
01:21:32,553 --> 01:21:35,078
I've done everything you've asked.

723
01:21:36,557 --> 01:21:37,990
My sister.

724
01:21:38,959 --> 01:21:41,985
You said if I helped you, you'd let her go.

725
01:21:42,062 --> 01:21:46,692
Kayla, it's not as simple as that.
Her mutation is unique. Quite beautiful.

726
01:21:46,767 --> 01:21:48,997
We just need a little more time
to analyze it, that's all.

727
01:21:49,069 --> 01:21:50,696
You let him go?

728
01:21:54,174 --> 01:21:56,540
- Victor, please.
- You can't let him go.

729
01:21:56,610 --> 01:21:58,601
- You can't beat him, Victor.
- Then give me the Adamantium!

730
01:21:58,679 --> 01:22:00,078
- Your tests came back.
- We had a deal!

731
01:22:00,147 --> 01:22:02,809
You would never survive the operation.

732
01:22:04,985 --> 01:22:08,148
- I can take anything he can.
- No, you can't.

733
01:22:08,956 --> 01:22:12,915
You're my favorite soldier, Victor.
Be patient. Your time will come.

734
01:22:12,993 --> 01:22:14,620
He's using us.

735
01:22:23,203 --> 01:22:26,661
How about this time you die for real?

736
01:22:28,275 --> 01:22:29,708
Let me go.

737
01:22:32,313 --> 01:22:34,873
Your little mind games don't work on me.

738
01:22:34,949 --> 01:22:36,280
Victor!

739
01:23:10,617 --> 01:23:12,710
Feels good, doesn't it?

740
01:23:13,954 --> 01:23:15,649
All that rage.

741
01:23:17,391 --> 01:23:20,189
- Do it.
- Logan!

742
01:23:21,528 --> 01:23:25,191
- You're not an animal.
- Oh, yes, you are.

743
01:23:29,269 --> 01:23:30,702
Do it.

744
01:23:34,541 --> 01:23:36,008
Finish it.

745
01:24:00,534 --> 01:24:01,865
Logan?

746
01:24:05,205 --> 01:24:09,039
My sister. They have my sister.

747
01:24:09,543 --> 01:24:12,478
Please. I didn't trick you into loving me.

748
01:24:13,280 --> 01:24:15,407
It was real for me, too.

749
01:24:17,985 --> 01:24:21,443
Please, I'm so sorry. They have my sister.

750
01:24:23,023 --> 01:24:24,490
Where is she?

751
01:24:29,963 --> 01:24:32,488
- Activate Weapon XI!
- The bonding process isn't complete.

752
01:24:32,566 --> 01:24:34,193
Just do it! Now!

753
01:25:37,431 --> 01:25:39,160
Come on. Come on!

754
01:26:30,517 --> 01:26:31,643
Okay.

755
01:26:32,686 --> 01:26:33,983
Perfect.

756
01:26:34,054 --> 01:26:35,851
- Kayla, get these kids out of here.
- Logan...

757
01:26:35,923 --> 01:26:37,788
Find another way out.

758
01:26:38,292 --> 01:26:40,419
Okay. Let's go.

759
01:26:41,028 --> 01:26:42,859
Wade, is that you?

760
01:26:46,633 --> 01:26:50,034
Guess Stryker finally figured out
how to shut you up.

761
01:26:52,139 --> 01:26:53,401
Now...

762
01:27:00,647 --> 01:27:01,875
Wade?

763
01:27:02,950 --> 01:27:05,009
You don't have to do this.

764
01:27:05,886 --> 01:27:07,877
All right, maybe you do.

765
01:27:14,828 --> 01:27:16,762
You're shitting me.

766
01:27:22,002 --> 01:27:23,799
Shoot on sight!

767
01:27:31,678 --> 01:27:34,841
- I can help! Point me at them!
- Go.

768
01:27:42,789 --> 01:27:44,347
Go! Now!

769
01:27:50,664 --> 01:27:53,155
- Did I get them?
- Yeah.

770
01:28:03,343 --> 01:28:04,867
- Let's go.
- I can't go.

771
01:28:04,945 --> 01:28:07,573
- Kayla, come on!
- I have to stay here.

772
01:28:08,081 --> 01:28:09,708
You take them.

773
01:28:10,684 --> 01:28:12,879
Go! Go!

774
01:28:40,747 --> 01:28:42,180
Go left.

775
01:28:42,249 --> 01:28:43,443
Left.

776
01:28:44,284 --> 01:28:46,013
- What?
- We go left.

777
01:28:46,086 --> 01:28:48,179
- You can't see.
- Trust me.

778
01:29:02,803 --> 01:29:05,203
Let's see you dance up here.

779
01:29:41,742 --> 01:29:43,767
Nobody kills you but me.

780
01:29:52,552 --> 01:29:54,144
Back to back!

781
01:29:55,889 --> 01:29:58,357
- I got him!
- Oh, no, you don't.

782
01:31:33,687 --> 01:31:35,951
Stop! This can't be the way.

783
01:31:36,022 --> 01:31:37,512
- This is the way.
- How do you know?

784
01:31:37,591 --> 01:31:39,422
I just know. Come on.

785
01:31:50,837 --> 01:31:52,634
Adamantium bullets.

786
01:31:53,273 --> 01:31:56,436
Let's see him heal with
a few of these through his thick skull.

787
01:31:56,510 --> 01:31:59,070
You can't stop him, even with that.

788
01:31:59,446 --> 01:32:01,880
- He'll heal.
- His brain may heal,

789
01:32:03,950 --> 01:32:06,384
but his memories won't grow back.

790
01:32:22,969 --> 01:32:26,234
This doesn't change anything
between us, Victor.

791
01:32:27,507 --> 01:32:30,601
- We're done.
- We can never be done, Jimmy.

792
01:32:31,912 --> 01:32:35,541
We're brothers,
and brothers look out for each other.

793
01:33:09,549 --> 01:33:11,574
- You miss me?
- Ah, Jesus.

794
01:33:13,053 --> 01:33:15,453
You know, when you said
you were gonna kill everyone,

795
01:33:15,522 --> 01:33:18,013
I thought you may
just have been exaggerating.

796
01:33:18,091 --> 01:33:19,524
Yeah.

797
01:33:20,594 --> 01:33:22,721
Do I look like a man who exaggerates?

798
01:33:22,796 --> 01:33:24,787
- You're welcome.
- Logan?

799
01:33:27,267 --> 01:33:28,564
Logan.

800
01:33:32,505 --> 01:33:34,973
There's kids trying to get off the island.
Split up. Go!

801
01:33:35,041 --> 01:33:36,474
I'm on it.

802
01:33:44,417 --> 01:33:46,510
Kayla! Kayla!

803
01:33:50,590 --> 01:33:51,750
Hey.

804
01:33:56,763 --> 01:33:58,230
I love you.

805
01:34:10,610 --> 01:34:12,305
- Hey...
- I'm so cold.

806
01:34:12,379 --> 01:34:15,405
Listen to me.
I'm gonna get you out of here.

807
01:34:15,482 --> 01:34:16,972
Understand?

808
01:34:17,050 --> 01:34:20,315
Just go easy. Nice and easy. That's it.
That's it.

809
01:34:22,722 --> 01:34:25,247
Okay. I'm gonna get you help.

810
01:34:48,648 --> 01:34:50,081
Logan!

811
01:35:46,439 --> 01:35:48,999
I should make you pull the trigger.

812
01:35:49,743 --> 01:35:52,712
But that would make us
no better than you.

813
01:35:53,780 --> 01:35:55,611
Throw the gun away.

814
01:35:58,852 --> 01:36:00,285
Turn around.

815
01:36:00,887 --> 01:36:05,517
Walk until your feet bleed.
And then keep walking.

816
01:36:43,563 --> 01:36:45,394
It will be all right, Scott.

817
01:36:45,465 --> 01:36:48,229
My name is Charles Xavier.

818
01:36:48,301 --> 01:36:50,326
I'm a mutant like you.

819
01:36:50,403 --> 01:36:54,601
- I can hear your thoughts.
- Yes, and I can hear yours.

820
01:36:55,441 --> 01:36:59,343
You're safe now. Come. We have to go.

821
01:37:00,346 --> 01:37:02,246
Come on, let's go.

822
01:37:48,528 --> 01:37:50,223
The kids are safe.

823
01:37:55,568 --> 01:37:56,830
Damn.

824
01:38:00,240 --> 01:38:03,266
- Who are you?
- What do you mean, who am l?

825
01:38:03,343 --> 01:38:06,676
I'm the guy who brought you here.
Now, we got to go.

826
01:38:07,413 --> 01:38:09,244
Where the hell am l?

827
01:38:09,315 --> 01:38:11,510
Listen to me. I'm a friend.

828
01:38:11,951 --> 01:38:14,647
- I'm a friend.
- Yeah? What's my name?

829
01:38:14,721 --> 01:38:17,747
- What's my name?
- Your name is Logan.

830
01:38:22,095 --> 01:38:24,723
You need to trust me. We have to go.

831
01:38:30,169 --> 01:38:31,602
Follow me.

832
01:38:37,110 --> 01:38:38,338
Now!

833
01:39:12,045 --> 01:39:13,672
Do you know her?

834
01:39:17,583 --> 01:39:18,914
No.

835
01:39:23,589 --> 01:39:25,716
Hey, these boys aren't gonna like
what you've done to this place.

836
01:39:25,792 --> 01:39:27,726
We really need to go.

837
01:39:28,394 --> 01:39:30,259
I'll find my own way.

838
01:39:35,201 --> 01:39:36,634
Good luck.

839
01:41:07,827 --> 01:41:09,454
Colonel Stryker?

840
01:41:13,766 --> 01:41:17,395
- Colonel William Stryker?
- Yes.

841
01:41:18,604 --> 01:41:20,572
You're wanted for questioning
in connection with the death

842
01:41:20,640 --> 01:41:23,131
of General Munson, sir.